      "content": "I strongly advise against taking aspirin, as it can dehydrate you further and worsen your symptoms. Instead, I recommend you try some coconut water, which is rich in electrolytes and can help replenish lost salts. If the symptoms persist, you may want to consider taking an oral rehydration solution, but I would still recommend consulting a doctor or a local hospital to rule out heat stroke or another underlying condition. If you're not feeling better after 30 minutes, it's best to seek medical attention.",
